sentences: Frederik Philip Carl August Barth  (1775 – December 22, 1804) was a German-Danish virtuoso oboist and composer.
Born in Kassel, Barth was trained by his father and played solo at a concert at the Royal Theater as a 14-year-old in 1789 and joined the chapel in 1793.
Born in Kassel, Barth was trained by his father and played solo at a concert at the Royal Theater as a 14-year-old in 1789 and joined the chapel in 1793.
He and his father directed in the years 1794-97 concerts in the Holstein Dramatic Society, which included various compositions by him.
